================================================================================

Subject to Section 3 below, you, as an individual, may:

  (a) Browse the Software publicly on the hosting platform where this
      repository is published.

  (b) Clone or download a single working copy of the Software solely to
      read, run, and study it on your own personal computer for the sole
      purpose of learning how it is built.

  (c) Quote short, attributed excerpts of the source code or documentation
      in commentary, critique, technical reviews, educational material,
      academic papers, or similar good-faith editorial contexts, subject
      to applicable fair-use / fair-dealing law in your jurisdiction.

  (d) Submit issues, security reports, or pull requests to the upstream
